## NestJS Backend Guidelines

Use current NestJS patterns with GraphQL (code-first) and Prisma.

- Keep modules cohesive: one domain per module with its resolver/service.
- Put business logic in services; resolvers/controllers stay thin.
- Use DTOs/InputTypes for all GraphQL inputs and outputs; avoid exposing Prisma models directly.
- Prefer dependency injection over static helpers; inject shared services.
- Use `PrismaService` for data access; wrap multi-step writes in `$transaction`.
- Validate inputs with `class-validator`; fail fast on invalid args.
- Enforce auth/roles with guards and decorators; never trust client IDs.
- Prefer explicit error handling and meaningful GraphQL errors.
- Keep naming consistent: `*.resolver.ts`, `*.service.ts`, `*.module.ts`, `dto/`, `entities/`.
